      <title>Weapons of Legend - Past Zelda Gear (Standalone)</title>
      <author>Tach9</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/455944</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/455944#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">10f927a39b397feea56ccacd6e99bcc3a0bbcb03</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 10:10:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6510770cbcda5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6510770adaf57.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/65029c5545982.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64f37484aadc5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64f3746d527c7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64ed47c6e4cc9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64ea41e46c4e3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e786910cfe7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64bdf47779cbf.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64d2f99991379.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64cc020e41e4c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64cc020e39ce2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c9f6637eeff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c9f717b810c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c31a7a963f2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c74ae81c7e2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c56500ac806.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c56489b2e9f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c200c005857.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c200c47fe81.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c200c4be811.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c200c2215ff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c0bb84a9ab5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64ba1a219b1db.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64ba1a0b54250.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64ba1acad8754.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64c200c54fc53.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; v4.0 - Returning&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;This update is a quick and dirty addition of initial compatibility for TKMM. I did a quick test and it seemed to work for me, but I'll work on polishing it up a bit more in the coming days.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As for more on my return, check the pinned comment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Initial TKMM Support&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is what will likely be the largest project that I carry out in Tears of the Kingdom modding and one that is largely motivated by nostalgia and a passion to learn new things. In a final version of this mod, I plan to bring many past swords, shields, bows, and potentially other items from past Zelda games into Tears of the Kingdom as standalone weapons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;u&gt;All items are available from the &lt;b&gt;Bargainer Statue at Lookout Landing for poes.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;This should give an ample incentive for exploring the depths and collecting poes as you go.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Breakable Weapons:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A separate download includes pack files to make most weapons breakable. Drop the romfs folder from this folder into the main folder. Currently a few updates behind. I will update at some point.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Visible Bows:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A separate download includes pack files to make the bows of this mod, and the quiver visible, drop its romfs folder into the main download's folder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Functional Mirror Shields:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A separate download includes pack files to re-enable the light reflecting ability of the mirror shields. Drop the romfs folder from this folder into the main mod folder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unbreakable Razor Sword:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A separate download includes a pack file to make the Razor Sword unbreakable. Just drop it in your mods folder and overwrite the one from the main mod.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;What's included:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Icons for all added weapons&lt;br&gt;(Modified Textures for most if not all models at this point).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Legend of Zelda:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-White Sword (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;-Shield of the Hero (Cross Shield) (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/174392"&gt;Pik Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Zelda II:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Magical Sword (Issuelink Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Link's Awakening:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Mirror Shield (Asalazar Model)&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A Link to the Past:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Fighter's Sword (Asalazar Custom Model)&lt;br&gt;-Fighter's Shield (Asalazar Custom Model)&lt;br&gt;-Red Shield (Asalazar Custom Model)&lt;br&gt;-Master Sword (Issuelink's OoT Master Sword, heavily edited by me)&lt;br&gt;-Mirror Shield (Issuelink Model)&lt;br&gt;-Ganon's Trident (Hyrule Warriors Model w/ Custom Textures by me)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ocarina of Time:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Kokiri Sword (Smash Ultimate Model)&lt;br&gt;-Boomerang (Smash Ultimate Model)&lt;br&gt;-Fairy Bow (Smash Ultimate Model w/ Rigging by Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;-Master Sword (Issuelink Model w/ Edits By Me)&lt;br&gt;-Deku Shield (Smash Ultimate Model)&lt;br&gt;-Hylian Shield of Time (New model from MessyProduct and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;-Megaton Hammer (New model from Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;-Gerudo Mirror Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/167938"&gt;Issuelink Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;-Crescent Mirror Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/167940"&gt;Issuelink Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;-Phantom Ganon Trident (Asalazar Custom Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Majora's Mask:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Kokiri Sword (MM) (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;-Ikana Mirror Shield (Edited Issuelink Model)&lt;br&gt;-Razor Sword (&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Breakable (100 Durability)&lt;/span&gt;) (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/443079"&gt;Asalazar Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;-Hero's Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/443079"&gt;Asalazar Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;-Gilded Sword (Issuelink Model)&lt;br&gt;-Hero's Bow (MM) (Asalazar Model)&lt;br&gt;-Great Fairy Sword (Issuelink Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Wind Waker:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Master Sword (Edited Smash Ultimate Model)&lt;br&gt;-Mirror Shield (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;-Skull Hammer (WWHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Ganondorf's Swords (WWHD Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Phantom Hourglass:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Phantom Sword (Edited Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;-Island Lobster Shield (Wooden Shield) (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spirit Tracks:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Lokomo Sword (Edited Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;-Shield (Spirit Tracks Model)&lt;br&gt;-Phantom Weapons (Smash Ultimate (Zelda Down-B) Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Twilight Princess:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Ordon Sword (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Ordon Shield (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Hylian Shield of Twilight (TPHD Model w/ Edits by Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;-Master Sword of Twilight (Issuelink Sword Model, Asalazar Sheath Model)&lt;br&gt;-Hero's Bow (Twilight Princess) (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Darknut Sword/Shield (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Skyward Sword:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Sacred Bow (SSHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Goddess Shield (SSHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Demise's Sword (SSHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Ghirahim's Sword (SSHD Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Breath of the Wild:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Bow of Light&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Necessary RSDB, Mals, and Resource Table files for 1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.2.0, 1.2.1&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u class="SelectedElement"&gt;Potential Future Plans:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Legend of Zelda:&lt;br&gt;-Magical Sword (Hyrule Warriors Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Wind Waker:&lt;br&gt;-Hero's Sword&lt;br&gt;-Darknut Sword (WWHD Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Minish Cap/Four Swords:&lt;br&gt;-Four Sword&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Twilight Princess:&lt;br&gt;-Gale Boomerang (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Wooden Sword (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Wooden Shield (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;-Twilight Scimitar (TPHD Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Skyward Sword:&lt;br&gt;-Master Sword (Unawakened)&lt;br&gt;-Goddess Sword&lt;br&gt;-Goddess Longsword&lt;br&gt;-Wooden/Iron Shields&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Merging With Other Mods:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;I have added some cursory&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://tkmm.org/docs/index.html"&gt;TKMM&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;support in the main mod download. I did a quick test and it seemed to work, but it's very much thrown together right now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For the purposes of merging with other mods I have included various files to aid in this process.&lt;br&gt;Files for aiding in merging are in the Merging Txt Files download. Those include the RSDB files.txt file which shows the changes I made to the RSDB files and the Mals.txt file which shows the changes I have made to the language files.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Tested on Yuzu, Ryujinx, and Homebrew Switch With Versions 1.1.0, 1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.2.0, and 1.2.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Known Issues&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Dropping Master Swords or the Phantom or Lokomo sword will result in them simply vanishing. They will not be dropped from lightning, however, so this issue will only pop up if you intentionally drop them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-OoT/MM Mirror Shields appear dark in the inventory screen. I am not sure if this is possible to fix, but I am looking into it on the side.</description>
